-- Sumitomo Metal Mining Says Won’t Buy Copper Ore From BHP in 2012
-- B y   J a e   H u r
-- 2012-01-17T07:28:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-17/sumitomo-metal-mining-says-won-t-buy-copper-ore-from-bhp-in-2012.html
Sumitomo Metal Mining Co. (5713) , Japan’s
second-largest copper producer, will not purchase concentrate
from  BHP Billiton Ltd. (BHP)  this year under an annual contract after
failing to reach an agreement on processing fees, company
spokesman Masashi Takahashi said today by phone. He declined to
disclose the tonnage under discussion.  A call to Kelly Quirke, a Melbourne-based spokeswoman for
BHP, was not answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jae Hur in Tokyo at 
 jhur1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
